projects.description:
Market reviews, strategy, action plan development and implementation support (interim management) for attracting new business activity for multiple public entities, economic development and Investment Promotion Agencies, both from the Netherlands and from Europe and abroad. 

Proposition, strategy and action plan development for the German market
▼Province of Gelderland: Identify opportunities to intensify the cooperation with North Rhine Westphalia in the logistics sectors – area business model analysis, road map development and activity support;
▼Port of Amsterdam: Analyze market opportunities, develop propositions and action plans aimed at the German market for different port clusters – proposition development, strategy and action-plan development;
▼Technical University Delft: Identify potential cooperation partners in Germany (multinational companies and competence networks) - survey;
▼WestHolland Foreign Investment Agency: Identify opportunities to attract corporate activities, real estate investment, tourism&conventions and international institutions in the German market for the Greater The Hague area – High level survey.  

Asian markets
▼WestHolland Foreign Investment Agency: Develop a proposition for the Technical University of Delft to attract R&D activities of a Korean multinational company – proposition development.

M&A real estate support and reviews of land development projects, including risk analysis, for multiple Dutch public and semi-public entities.

▼Japanese corporate client: Introduction to a Dutch start-up company and support with the participation transaction (cross cultural business support);
▼Private client: Sales strategy development and sales of real estate property in Province of Limburg, gaining trust, opening-up deadlock situation, support conclusion of transaction;
▼EY: Review business plan of start-up company.
